HJR77 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 COMMENDING UNITED STATES ARMY COMMAND SERGEANT MAJOR KEVIN
4 D. HARKEY ON HIS ACCOMPLISHMENTS.
5
6 WHEREAS, it is with profound appreciation and deepest
7 admiration that we recognize Command Sergeant Major (CSM)
8 Kevin D. Harkey for more than 30 honorable years of service
9 and leadership in the United States Army 710th Brigade
10 Support Battalion, 3rd Infantry Brigade Combat Team (Light
11 Infantry), 10th Mountain Division; and
12 WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished career, CSM
13 Harkey demonstrated unwavering dedication to duty, mission
14 accomplishment, and the welfare of soldiers and their
15 families; and
16 WHEREAS, CSM Kevin D. Harkey is a native of
17 Huntsville, Alabama; he enlisted in the U.S. Army in August
18 1990 as a 24N, Chaparral System Mechanic, and reclassified
19 as 68C, License Practical Nurse in 1996; his civilian
20 education includes an Associate's Degree in Information
21 Systems from Strayer University (Summa Cum Laude), a
22 Bachelor of Science Degree in Information Systems with dual
23 concentrations in Cybersecurity and Computer Networking with
24 a minor in business management from Strayer University
25 (Summa Cum Laude), and a Master's Degree in Cybersecurity
26 from Liberty University (Summa Cum Laude); and
27 WHEREAS, CSM Harkey's assignments include Chaparral
28 Systems Mechanic, later reclassified as a 14S, Avenger Crew
Page 1

Systems Mechanic, later reclassified as a 14S, Avenger Crew
HJR77 Enrolled
29 Member, C Battery 4/3 ADA, Kitzingen, Germany (1991-94);
30 68C, Licensed Practical Nurse Course, Fort Sam Houston,
31 Texas (1994-96); Medical/Surgical Nurse on Ward 4AB,
32 Blanchfield Army Community Hospital, Fort Campbell, Kentucky
33 (1996-98); Squad Leader/Wardmaster for ICW 3, 86th Combat
34 Support Hospital, Fort Campbell, Kentucky (1998-2001);
35 Critical Care Unit Nurse, Medical/Surgical Wardmaster (Ward
36 9 East), and Section NCO for the Department of Nursing,
37 William Beaumont Army Medical Center, Fort Bliss, Texas
38 (2001-05); Army Medical Department Directorate Proponency
39 NCO, Fort Sam Houston, Texas, with special duty at the Army
40 Human Resources Command, Alexandria, Virginia (2005-08);
41 Senior Clinical NCO (2008-09) and First Sergeant Warrior
42 Transition Unit, A Company (2009-11), DeWitt Army Community
43 Hospital, Fort Belvoir, Virginia; Medical and Senior
44 Clinical Operations NCO, 421st Multi-Functional Medical
45 Battalion, Baumholder, Germany (2011-14); Student, United
46 States Army Sergeants Major Academy, Class 65 (2014-15);
47 G-3/5/7 Operations SGM, Regional Health Command – Atlantic,
48 Fort Belvoir, Virginia (2015-18); and Command Sergeant
49 Major, 710th Brigade Support Battalion, Fort Polk, Louisiana
50 (2018-21); and
51 WHEREAS, his deployments include Physical
52 Examinations NCO, Medical Element, Honduras, JTF-Bravo
53 (2000); ICW Section NCO, 31st CSH, Operation Iraqi Freedom
54 (2004); and First Sergeant, Task Force Med (KFOR 17,
55 MNBGEast), Operation Joint Guardian, Kosovo (2013-14); and
56 WHEREAS, CSM Harkey's military education includes the
