57 Chaparral Systems Mechanic (24N) course; Licensed Practical
58 Nurse (68C) course; Warrior Leader's course, Advanced
59 Leader's course, Senior Leader's course; the Master Fitness
60 Trainer's course; Air Assault course, Emergency Medical
61 Technician-Basic course; Warrior Transition course; Medical
62 NCO Mid-Managers course; Equal Opportunity Leader's course;
63 Master Resiliency Trainer course; and United States Army
64 Sergeants Major Academy; and
65 WHEREAS, his awards, decorations, and achievements
66 include medals for Meritorious Service (4 OLC), Army
67 Commendation, Joint Service Accommodation, Army Achievement
68 (5 OLC), Kosovo Campaign, Iraq Campaign, Global War on
69 Terrorism, and NATO; badges for Combat Action, Expert Field
70 Medical, Air Assault, and German Schutzenschnur-Gold; and
71 other commendations such as the Order of Military Medical
72 Merit (O2M3), Sergeant Audie Murphy Club Member (1999),
73 101st Airborne Division (Assault) NCO of the Year (1999),
74 101st Corp Support Group NCO of the Year (1999), and 86th
75 CSH NCO of the Year (1999); and
76 WHEREAS, CSM Harkey has two sons, Lundon and
77 Prinston; a daughter, Kristan; and seven grandchildren,
78 DaeShawn, Duran, Tristan, Kiaylah, Prinston, Tailyn, and
79 Kylei; his hobbies and interests are working out, martial
80 arts, chess, jazz, and home improvement projects; he is also
81 a member of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Incorporated; and
82 WHEREAS, CSM Harkey's last day on active duty in the
83 United States Army was October 31, 2021, and his first day
84 as a retiree was November 1, 2021; throughout his career,
